					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Currently, submappers are used to fix old mis-defined NES 1.0 roms.<br />In future, similar mis-definitions might occur also in NES 2.0 roms.<br />So, I think, even in NES 2.0 files, submapper numbers should be kept reserved for future bugfixes.<br /><br />BNROM... I think it was originally defined as mapper 7 (AOROM), I've seen an old Deadly Towers rom-image from 1997 assigned like so, and then somebody &quot;corrected&quot; it by assigning it as mapper 34 (NINA-001). In so far, both mapper 7 and 34 may need a BNROM submapper number.</div>

